Seems like a spot that would be good to bring friends to get drinks and a variety of tacos. I would say less good as a spot to just order takeout (unfortunate given the current COVID state of the world).  Food was fine. My burrito was kinda lame. Rice and beans were cold and uninspired. The chicken (Pollo Pibil) was pretty good, but nothing crazy and didn't make up for the plain flavor of the rice, beans, and salsa fresca. The taco I ordered (Al Pastor) was good. I wish there was more pineapple. The pork overpowered the pineapple, but that might be just me lol.  Also, I grabbed an order of the Three Cheese Tequila Queso. Got back to my place, did not have any chips. I assumed it would come with chips because it is under the "Chips" section of the online menu and was $8.00. The menu is not clear as to whether chips are free and I am supposed to ask for them, or if chips are only included with items that explicitly say they come with chips (Solo Salsa & Chips, Chips & Guac, Nachos, etc.). Either way, it is silly that I would have to explicitly ask for chips with the dip I ordered, or obnoxious to have to pay for chips separately on top an $8.00 dip.

Got the nachos to our destination, laid them out, toppings still warm, tasting amazing!  Definitely order them deconstructed and put them together at home. Chips are still crisp and the flavors won’t be beat!  Will continue to come back to the patio and bring food home for when we want to indulge in the margaritas on our porch!

This was the worst experience. Preordered for curbside pick up. Arrived at pick up time. No curbside, had to wait outside in the cold or in a room close in proximity to too many others- definitely not social distancing guidelines- in the same situation, waiting well over our scheduled pick up time. One food runner, a bartender back up bringing orders without a face mask. At least half of the cooks or those putting orders together did not have masks on. No communication, no compensation offered such as a free drink or whatever, just wait for your food that you already paid for in these conditions or leave. If it was more than you could have handled you should have limited the amount of orders that could be placed. At the very least, follow the guidelines, wear masks, wear gloves, have hand sanitizer available for the food runner that is handling every customers order. DST lacked common sense & customer service, will never return.

Yikes!  We were so excited to come here this evening and it turned out to be one of the worst dining experiences I’ve had in a while!  We were promptly seated and the server was friendly and quickly took our order.  We had chips and guacomole served soonafter, but then we waited and waited and waited.  Well over an hour we waited for our entre’s and still nothing.  Pretty much every other table seated around us (with folks that arrived after we were seated) had been served and yet, we still waited.  We asked to speak with a manager soon after, and he was apologetic and explained that another large party had been seated and slowed things down in the kitchen (which seemed odd, given that the restaurant was only half full with many open tables).  The manager acknowledged that this wasn’t a good excuse and assured us that our food would be out shortly and continued to offer his apologies.  We still waited another solid twenty minutes before our entre’s finally arrived and while we held onto hope that the food would be well worth the wait, it was certainly not.  Most of the tacos and burritos were cold, the fajita’s were not sizzling and everything was over salted to the point that the dishes were barely edible.  Thankfully, the manager didn’t charge us for anything we were served when we expressed our displeasure with the condition and quality of our food.  While I can appreciate that the manager seemed to own up to the fact that what we experienced was unacceptable, it really made for a horrible end to our evening.  The ambience and atmosphere of this place is really great, but they seemed so disorganized and lost tonight.  I’ve since seen that many others have shared similar experiences, so unless this crew can right the ship quickly they seem to be headed down a path that doesn’t lead to good things for anyone.  An update in response to the owner:  what an odd, inappropriate and totally confusing response!  I wasn’t trashing your restaurant at all - just simply stating the truth of our experience.  The fact that we weren’t charged for the food that we didn’t eat (I can send you the photos we took of our un eaten food if you’d like) doesn’t excuse what we experienced.  In fact, when you have to write “I’m not making excuses” - you are basically making excuses.   If I had posted a five star review - that would be me being dishonest.  My response was just an honest telling of what we experienced - if you don’t like it, then do a better job to change what your customers experience.  Also - it doesn’t sound like you were there at the restaurant, so clearly you weren’t there to see all of the empty tables both upstairs and on the outside patio.  I’ve been at many full restaurants (with people waiting to be seated) and have never had to wait for as long as we waited for an entree to be delivered. For me - this means that you are either understaffed or there is a serious disorganization problem in your kitchen.  Also, I’m not Native American - but I have no idea why that would be relevant in any way, shape or form (it’s just so random and unrelated - it would be like me writing “I also have red shoes and breath air!”).  I am 100% confident that your response to my initial review is abnormal - a customer service based owner would have simply replied that they regretted the bad experience the customer had and would have pledged to work harder to ensure that they wouldn’t have the same experience again if they were ever gracious enough to return for a second try (instead of attacking them and essentially calling them liars). I truly wish you all the best of luck, but ensure you that you will need to change the way you serve and interact with your customers if you want your business to survive in the competitive and customer driven restaurant industry.

I visited this location for a gathering with friends. We got there a little later than others who were already seated together inside. There was not enough room for my fiancé, myself, and a friend to sit with the group and all the other tables were either occupied or reserved. We were told that we could sit outside. The waitress took our orders and then the three of us went out to the patio to find a table. My friend ordered just an alcoholic drink. My fiancé and I ordered a pitcher of frozen margaritas and two orders of chicken and steak combo fajitas. The margaritas were okay and WAY overpriced at $38! We then got our fajitas and they were not good. Our friend tried some and she didn’t think they were good either. They just had this funky kind of taste to them, it’s difficult to explain. I would have brought this to the attention of our waitress but she never returned! She never asked how anything was or refilled our waters. Then we get the bill and see we were charged 18% gratuity. We all didn’t agree with that charge because we didn’t sit with the group inside and our waitress could care less about us. I just wanted to leave and didn’t feel like getting into a confrontation with anyone so we paid and left. Very disappointing experience. We will never be back. This is the easiest review I've ever written for a restaurant. Deep South Taco is hands down my favorite restaurant in Buffalo. They've gotten so many things right: the overall branding/design of the restaurant is amazing, the food is delicious, and the service is top notch. Deep South has become at least a once-a-week destination for us; we've never had a bad experience.  Some advice: Always, always, always order the nachos. I literally dream about them.  More advice: Check out brunch. Some of the best (and must unique) breakfast food in the city. The churro french toast is heaven. And...ummm...they have breakfast nachos. So. Dang. Good.  My only criticism is that they serve beer in plastic cups, which makes the beer warm up pretty fast. I grumble about it to myself every time we go...but the food/service/space more than makes up for the plastic cups :)
